{
  "stem": "15768.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so the logical route escape, we felt, or my father felt, was to, to go to Paris and hook up with family there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was convinced after going through World War I that the Germans would not go beyond the Maginot Line.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And with that thought in mind, we set out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Actually, the first leg of our trip, four other people and ourselves, another family of four, chipped in and paid a pommes frites, which is the, the potato chip people that stand in the street with a cart.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We paid him off to try and drive us in the direction of the border.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We really just barely got to the outskirts of Brussels when the roads were so clogged with people walking, escaping, French troops coming in the direction of Brussels because this-- the British and the French were, at that point, of course, in the war.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he sort of gave up the ghost.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The car gave up the ghost.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It overheated and died.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so he was generously paid off.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he left us to go back to Brussels to his family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we continued on with just the barest necessity-- a pillowcase for each with some belongings.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we walked.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On foot, we walked along with everyone else, heading towards the border.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Along the way, we were strafed We'd have to dive into the ditch.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on a number of occasions, I found myself next to someone who had been hit and was dead.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we moved along, night and day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some of the good-hearted farmers gave us children milk to drink, gave the adults water to drink.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because we were a pretty bedraggled bunch, really.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
